.TH "build_hdr_data" 9 "build_hdr_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
build_hdr_data \- creates L2/L3/L4 header data buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" build_hdr_data
.BI "(u8 hdr_field "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "int *hdr_len "  ","
.BI "u8 *hdr_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdr_field" 12
bitfield determining needed headers
.IP "skb" 12
socket buffer
.IP "hdr_len" 12
array of header lengths
.IP "hdr_data" 12
buffer to write the header to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads hdr_field to determine which headers are needed by firmware.
Builds a buffer containing these headers.  Saves individual header
lengths and total buffer length to be used to build descriptors.
